'''Abraham, Ethnus, Acrates, James, and John''' are [[martyr]]s venerated in [[Ethiopia]] as [[saint]]s. Their feast day is August 3 in the [[Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria|Coptic Church]].

==References==
*Holweck, F. G. ''A Biographical Dictionary of the Saints''. St. Louis, MO: B. Herder Book Co. 1924.

