{{Politics of Bermuda}}
A '''referendum on the [[death penalty]]''' for [[premeditated murder]] was held in [[Bermuda]] on 12 August 1990.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=bm011990 Bermuda, 12 August 1990: Retention/abolition of the death penalty] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref> The referendum was held following pressure from the [[United Kingdom|British]] government, and was held as part of the Capital Punishment Referendum Act, 1989.<ref>[http://www.commonlii.org/bm/legis/consol_act/cpra1989304/ Capital Punishment Referendum Act 1989] Bermuda Consolidated Legislation</ref> However, voters approved of retaining the penalty, with 79% voting in favour.
The death penalty was later abolished by the [[Parliament of Bermuda]] following a vote in December 1999.<ref name=DD/>
