{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | image = Diploporaceae - Diplopora annulata.JPG | image_width = 250px | image_caption = Fossil of ''Diplopora annulata'' from Triassic of Italy | fossil_range = [[Silurian]] – [[Jurassic]] {{fossilrange|426.2|155.7}} | domain = [[Eukaryota]] | regnum = [[Viridiplantae]] | phylum = [[Chlorophyta]] | classis = [[Ulvophyceae]] | ordo = [[Dasycladales]] | familia = [[Diploporaceae]] | genus = '''''Diplopora''''' | genus_authority = [[Karl Emil von Schafhäutl|K.E. Schafhäutl]], 1863 }}
'''''Diplopora''''' is a genus of marine [[Dasycladaceae|dasycladacean]] algae in the family [[Diploporaceae]].<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/108416394 GBIF]</ref><ref name="Oregon fossils">{{cite book|last1=Orr|first1=Elizabeth L.|last2=Orr|first2=William N.|title=Oregon fossils|date=2009|publisher=Oregon State University Press|location=Corvallis|isbn=9780870715730|edition=2nd|pages=7–8}}<!--|accessdate=23 November 2014--></ref><ref name="UMPC">{{cite web |url=http://www.cas.umt.edu/paleontology/browse.cfm?field=taxonname&value=Diplopora%20oregonensis |title=The University of Montana Paleontology Center|accessdate=23 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=Erik Flügel |author2=Baba Senowbari-Daryan |author3=George D. Stanley, Jr. |year=1989 |title=Late Triassic dasycladacean alga from northeastern Oregon: significance of first reported occurrence in western North America |journal=[[Journal of Paleontology]] |volume=63 |issue=3 |pages=374–381 |jstor=1305509}}</ref>
==Fossil records== This genus is known in the fossil records from the [[Silurian]] to the [[Jurassic]] (from about 426.2 to 155.7 million years ago). Fossils of species within this genus have been found in Europe, Iran, Japan, Mexico, Russia, Iraq and United States.<ref name=AA>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=54813 Paleobiology Database]</ref>
==Species== Species within this genus include:<ref name=AA/> * ''[[Diplopora oregonensis]] E. Flügel et al. * ''[[Diplopora permica]] Korde 1965 * ''[[Diplopora annulata]] Schafhäutl <ref>M Herak - 1957 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/1484328?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents Some Problems in the Dasyclad Genus Diplopora]</ref>
