{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Use British English|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = James Abbott | image = | fullname = | birth_date = 1892 | birth_place = [[Patricroft]], England | death_date = | position = Inisde-right | years1 = | clubs1=Barton Albion| caps1=~ | goals1 = | years2 = | clubs2=[[Eccles United F.C.|Eccles Borough]] | caps2=~ | goals2 = | years3 = 1913 | clubs3=[[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]| caps3=3 | goals3 = 2 }} '''James Abbott''' (born 1892, date of death unknown) was a [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[Football League]] for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. He was born in [[Patricroft]], England.<ref>*Joyce, Michael: "The Football League player's records 1888 to 1939 " ({{ISBN|1899468676}}).</ref>
He played in three top flight games for Manchester City, prior to the outbreak of World War One, scoring two goals in three games, including a goal on his debut at Sheffield United in September 1913. He had moved to the Hyde Road club after non-League spells with Barton Albion and [[Eccles United F.C.|Eccles Borough]].
