{{Infobox college coach | name = Samuel E. Abbott | image = | alt = | caption = | sport = [[American football|Football]] | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = | coach_years1 = 1905 | coach_team1 = [[Northern Colorado Bears football|Colorado Normal]] | overall_record = 0–2–2 | bowl_record = | tournament_record = | championships = | awards = | coaching_records = }} '''Samuel E. Abbott''' was an [[American football]] coach. He served as the head football coach at the State Normal School of Colorado—now known as the [[University of Northern Colorado]]—in [[Greeley, Colorado]] for one season, from 1905, compiling a record of 0–2–2.<ref>{{Cite web |last = DeLassus |first = David |title = Northern Colorado Bears Records By Year |publisher = [[College Football Data Warehouse]] |url = http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_iaa/bigsky/northern_colorado/coaching_records.php |accessdate = April 24, 2013 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140108013139/http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_iaa/bigsky/northern_colorado/coaching_records.php |archivedate = January 8, 2014 |df = }}</ref>
